                <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72119/5371: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Commission to Negotiate Peace</gloss>
                        to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-06-19T19:00:00+01:00"
                            >June 19, 1919—7 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 8:42 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2651. [From Lansing.] For your information. Referring to Mission’s number 2562 of
                    June 13th, 1919.<note n="49" xml:id="d266fn49">Not printed.</note> Treaty with
                    Germany in final form released in full to press this afternoon for publication
                    Friday morning<note n="49a" xml:id="d266fn49a">June 20.</note> in accordance
                    with decision by Council of Principal Allied and Associated Powers to publish at
                    earliest possible date after release <pb facs="0631" n="593" xml:id="pg_593"/>
                    of German counter proposal and reply thereto. Ten copies of proof copy, first
                    print, of final treaty forwarded you by courier this afternoon. Additional
                    copies will be sent as soon as obtained. Lansing.</p>
                <closer>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Mission</hi>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
